- id: '2069153080323781017'
  text: Tux, my healthy, gorgeous, 8 year old Tuxedo died suddenly. One minute he
    was looking at me with his beautiful bright eyes and the next thing I knew he
    fell off his perch and was dead when he hit the floor. I just can’t believe it.
    I’m 70, retired and he was my companion. My vet said it is not uncommon for cats
    to die suddenly due to hidden heart issues. That’s what they think happened. The
    hidden blessing is that he didn’t have time to suffer. I’ve had cats all my life
    but Tux was more than a cat. He was my sweet boy. Thanks for listening.
